Coronavirus Prevention Toolkit for Parents

Carter County Drug Prevention Coalition
March 20 at 10:12 AM ·

Hey parents!

Did you know that research shows ONE conversation about drugs, tobacco or alcohol can be the difference in a child's decision to use these substances for the first time? Did you know that 55% of Carter County teens reported via school survey last year that they had NEVER had this conversation?

This resource guide, compiled by Carter County Drug Prevention, with resources from Kids Health, NIDA and Partnership for Drug Free Kids will help you to have this conversation while you’re stuck at home!

Tennessee Department of Health
December 12, 2019 at 4:43 PM ·

Are you familiar with ACEs? Adverse Childhood Experiences, or ACEs are potentially traumatic events that occur in childhood (0-17 years) such as experiencing violence, abuse or neglect; witnessing violence in the home; and having a family member attempt or die by suicide. Adverse Childhood Experiences have been linked to risky health behaviors, chronic health conditions, low life potential and early death.

post_text: Check out this awesome article in Outside Magazine about the Healthy Parks Healthy Person initiative in Tennessee State Parks! We are lucky to have several state parks close by to take advantage of this wonderful program.
shared_text:
Healthy Parks Healthy Person TN
April 30, 2019 at 8:08 AM ·

Healthy Parks Healthy Person and Tennessee State Parks were mentioned in a large spread in the latest Outside Magazine! Although we can't share the entire article here for you, it is a great story about how healthcare providers across the country are beginning to utilize the power of nature to heal. Our program is mentioned as one on the cutting edge of this growing movement!
Head out to your local store and pick up a copy! It is a fantastic read.

post_text:
The Tennessee State Parks are part of a movement called Healthy Parks Healthy Person (on a national level, it is known as Healthy Parks Healthy People). Research has shown that getting outside and being active are good for overall health, and with Healthy Parks Healthy Person, citizens of our great state are encouraged to visit their local parks and get moving!

With the Healthy Parks Healthy Person TN app, you can track your activities, such as walking, biking, paddling, and so much more, to earn points. Earning points can get you real rewards that are redeemable in any Tennessee State Park. Visit their website http://healthyparkstn.com/ to find out more about how you can start getting outdoors and getting healthy, all while enjoying our beautiful and diverse public lands!

Looking for something to do this weekend? Take a walk on the Tweetsie Trail!

A rails-to-trails project, the Tweetsie Trail is a former part of the ET&WNC railroad that runs 10 miles between Johnson City and Elizabethton. It's the perfect trail for walking, running, or even biking, so get yourself, your friends, and your family outside and log some steps!

A rails-to-trails project, the Tweetsie Trail is a former part of the ET&WNC railroad that runs 10 miles between Johnson City and Elizabethton. It's the perfect trail for walking, running, or even biking, so get yourself, your friends, and your family outside and log some steps!

Tennessee Department of Health
July 16, 2018 at 1:22 PM ·

Feeling ugh? Monday blues getting to you? Perfect time to lace up those shoes and log some steps! Go for a walk!

post_text:
Need a quick meal this weekend?! Check out this recipe for Oven Roasted Chicken and Veggies! Share your favorite recipes using #GrowCarterCounty #HealthierTN
INGREDIENTS
2 large boneless skinless chicken breasts
1 red bell pepper
1 green bell pepper
1 yellow bell pepper
½ small red onion
1 medium zucchini
1 cup broccoli florets
½ cup grape tomatoes, sliced in half
2 tablespoons olive oil
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
2 teaspoons Italian seasoning
INSTRUCTIONS
Preheat oven to 475° F. Spray a large baking sheet with cooking spray.
Chop all the veggies into large pieces. On a separate plate or cutting board chop all the chicken in large cubes.
Place the chicken and veggies on the prepared baking sheet. Add the olive oil, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Toss to combine.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until the veggies are charred and chicken is cooked through.
Serve immediately and enjoy!

text:
Downtown Elizabethton Farmers Market
June 12, 2017 at 2:10 PM ·

FREE Kid's Event this Tuesday at the Market! From 5 - 8pm.

The UT Extension Carter County office will be hosting a game! Your child will receive a "Meet A Farmer" card at the UT Extension booth. They will then go and interview one of our farmers to complete the card. They can return it to the booth for a free, kid-sized market shopping bag!

The City of Elizabethton Fire Department will also be joining in on the fun! Kids can tour a firetruck, take a picture with a firefighter, and learn about fire safety.
